In blizzard conditions, these truckers travel over ice roads that often take them over frozen lakes. Each man is trained in self survival, from fixing his truck in sub zero conditions in seconds to escaping from a truck if the ice cracks. On the other end of the journey are miners whose lives depend on the truckers making it to their base, year after year. The episodes will form a narrative arch - taking the viewer on a journey from when the experienced and novice truckers first sign up for the season, to the last truck making it back to base.

programme.title: Outback Truckers
programme.desc: S8 E7 Episode 7 In the dead of night in Longreach north Queensland, long distance cattle transporters David and Kylie Hornick have hit trouble. programme.title: Outback Truckers
programme.desc: S8 E8 Episode 8 In central Queensland, husband and wife team Kylie and David Hornick, are feeling the pressure of a looming deadline on a monster job. In the last two days their convoy of trucks has racked up a whopping 2200 kilometres picking up and delivering 1224 head of cattle. Tempers are frayed as they push to meet their 3pm cut off. Trucker Mike Partridge is helping load a vintage 1948 Farmall tractor, one of 9 vintage tractors he's transporting to Western Australia. In Australia's tropical Northern Territory there's storm clouds on the horizon. It's not just rain that's troubling the Water Drillers, the pressure is on this hit and miss operation for the last bore hole to be a success.

programme.title: American Restoration
programme.desc: S4 E22 Break In Rick Dale, one of Pawn Stars' most popular experts, runs Las Vegas based Rick's Restorations, a family business that finds, restores and upcycles cool objects ranging from Cadillacs to Coke Machines. The before and after reveals of his work are always highlights, in part because of the history nuggets Rick Dale shares about each object, whether it's a barber chair or a gas pump. In this spinoff series, featuring the dynamic characters at Rick's workplace, viewers will watch a variety of objects be bought, bartered and transformed, learning the process of restoration; how do you duplicate Coke machine red? Where can you find 1920s tires? A storyteller who works with tools instead of a pen, Rick shares when and why objects were invented, who used them and how fixing or transforming them changes their value.

He'll head north to Wiluna with the final 200 kilometres on rough dirt roads. The short cut at this time of year is a massive gamble, the cyclone season is just beginning. New South Wales has been hit by its worst bush fires on record and it's also in the grip of a three year long drought. Farmers are struggling and in desperate need of hay to feed livestock. The army has arrived with 200 troops and Lance Corporal Matt Scheimer will command three of the nine trucks in the convoy. Mike Partridge is in the middle of hauling eight rare tractors, worth $130,000, 4000 kilometres to Western Australia. He has two more to load. The journey is further complicated by only being allowed to take one trailer on Victorian roads at a time.

programme.title: Mary Berry at 90: A Lifetime of Cooking
programme.desc: S1 E1 Tom Allen Dame Mary Berry takes a fond look back at her career in food while bringing viewers incredible mouth-watering recipes to try at home. Mary can trace her passion for outdoor cooking back 80 years, when she became a Girl Guide. Her friend, comedian Tom Allen, shares her love of the countryside but perhaps not the same aptitude for cooking. Together, they take a leisurely boat ride, sharing tales and facing the odd challenge as Tom attempts to drive the boat and navigate a lock. They stop along the way to cook Mary's classic pan-fried cod, which she learnt to make at college, and the star pudding of Mary's childhood, bread and butter pudding using her mother's recipe, which she still loves eating anywhere. Mary also makes her brand new Thai chicken traybake and her reinvention of her 1970s cottage pie with a modern mash. Spending time with Tom is a chance for Mary to share some rarely seen TV archive footage of her early attempts at outdoor cooking, showing how much things have changed.

Celebrated pastry chef and famous chocolatier, Tibballs presents an array of incredibly clever and innovative tricks, tips and cheats to bring the wow factor to home baking. Kirsten believes chocolate is the key to happiness, and with a selection of delectable desserts easy to recreate in home kitchens, she may just be right. Kirsten is sharing recipes and techniques for everything from a next-level take on white chocolate & peanut parfait to her rich chocolate flan. In series three of The Chocolate Queen, Tibballs shares a wealth of knowledge as she works through a huge range of recipes, ensuring even beginner bakers can successfully enjoy her creations at home.

programme.title: Rick Stein's Cornwall
programme.desc: S2 E12 Episode 12 Following in the footsteps of Turner, one of Britain's most loved artists, Rick discovers how much the Cornish landscape influenced his work. At Newlyn Fish Market Rick counts in the daily catch with the head auctioneer who tells him how the market has adapted to modern times. Surrounded by beautifully fresh fish, Rick takes away some monkfish and fires up his BBQ to make a grillade of monkfish with roasted red pepper sauce. At Caerhays Castle, home to the nation's largest collection of Magnolia plants, Rick discovers how this corner of Cornwall was once home to some of the great Victorian plant hunters.

programme.title: Food Safari
programme.desc: S2 E7 Croatian This program delves into the delicious world of Croatian food and Maeve enlists her friend Dennis Valcich, chef, author and passionate promoter of the food from his homeland, to run through the key ingredients used in the cuisine. He demonstrates a simple and delicious recipe from his home on the Dalmatian coast - artichoke cooked simply with potatoes and broad beans. Also from Dalmatia, Melbourne chef Ino Kuvacic, from Dalmatino Restaurant, who makes the dish beloved of all - a brodet: fish stew served on polenta. As well as the coastline, the inland of Croatia is represented with a range of smallgoods made by long-time king of Croatian smallgoods Ivan Spehar, who brought the famous skinless sausage cevapcici to many Australians. Home cook and matriarch Branka Roncevic makes the famous cabbage rolls which are served with creamy mashed potato. Her son Frank continues a family tradition of the big Sunday cookout using a bell-shaped Croatian outdoor oven called a peka, which transforms anything cooked in it into a masterpiece. Also using meat and flame, well-known restaurateur Tonci Farac, from Wildfire Restaurant on Sydney's Circular Quay, cooks a magnificent rack of lamb on the barbecue using salt and rosemary to add simple flavours. Prodigious sweets maker Mira Valcich whips up simple biscuits with a plum jam filling to finish.

programme.title: Food Safari
programme.desc: S2 E8 Singaporean This program sizzles with colour, flavour and texture as it savours the wonderful complexity of Singaporean food. Maeve meets up with two Singaporean friends to guide her through the range of ingredients: passionate home cook Helina Lee picks the top spices and sauces needed, while chef Alex Lee (Ginger and Spice, Singapore restaurant) shows off the range of fresh produce and seafood including mud crabs - which he transforms into the famous Singapore chilli mud crab with a surprise key ingredient. Top chef Chui Lee Luk from the acclaimed Claude's restaurant is better known for her French-style food, though away from work she makes a marvellous Assam fish, adapting her mother's treasured recipe. Barrister Tiffany Wong, one of the descendants of a famous Hainanese family, shows how to make beautifully tender Hainan chicken with chicken rice, served with fresh ginger and chilli sauces. Helina Lee whips up a fast salad snack beloved of Singaporeans called rojak. Along the way, we spend time with a Singaporean chef who almost dances as he juggles woks and flame at breakneck speed, and we learn about the love of hawker stalls serving beloved specials. Chef and cooking teacher Chee Ong then demonstrates a stylish take on the famous bubur cha-cha - a dessert of tropical fruit, tapioca and sweet potato that is simply divine.

Celebrated pastry chef and famous chocolatier, Tibballs presents an array of incredibly clever and innovative tricks, tips and cheats to bring the wow factor to home baking. Kirsten believes chocolate is the key to happiness, and with a selection of delectable desserts easy to recreate in home kitchens, she may just be right. Kirsten is sharing recipes and techniques for everything from a next-level take on white chocolate & peanut parfait to her rich chocolate flan. On the wild Atlantic coast, near Bedruthan Steps, Rick meets fellow chef Emily Scott who recreates the meal she cooked for President Joe Biden during the recent G7 summit. And Rick takes to the waves with an inspirational organisation who offer therapy using the power of surfing.

programme.title: Food Safari
programme.desc: S2 E9 Hungarian This program revels in centuries-old dishes cooked by passionate chefs and home cooks as it explores Hungarian cuisine. Maeve meets up with chef Stephen Oroszvari who has a one-man mission to excite the world about the flavours of his homeland. For instance, did you know that Hungarians are so passionate about paprika, that they have nicknames for some of their favourite varieties? 'Strong Stephen' and 'Gentle Anna' are just two. Long-time restaurateur Csaba Cserfalvi shares tips on making the perfect schnitzel and also shows how deeply committed Hungarians are to their carbs with a deep-fried langos bread and many variations on potatoes. Sport guru Les Murray shares the recipe for his mother's rakott krumpli, layered potatoes with csabai sausage and sour cream, and we join a mad, wonderful goulash cook-off, followed by Stephen's beautiful recipe for Porkolt, a form of goulash served with nokedli, or homemade pasta. The episode soars to a sweet, magnificent crescendo with some of the most exquisite delights made by artisans who have perfected strudels and layered cakes, beigli and tortes. Then, food editor and broadcaster Janelle Bloom shares her grandmother's recipe for wicked cream cheese and sour cherry strudel.

programme.title: Food Safari
programme.desc: S2 E10 Sri Lankan This program explores the colourful fresh flavours and seductive charm of Sri Lankan cooking. Maeve visits a fragrant spice emporium with top Australian Sri Lankan chef Peter Kuruvita, from Flying Fish restaurant, who hones in on the essentials. He whips up an elegant prawn curry with a creamy coconut sauce. We meet caterer, food reviewer and tour guide Paul Van Reyk who demonstrates how to grate a fresh coconut and uses it to make a simple vibrant sambol with a touch of chilli and a delicious, fresh green stir-fry with a handful of ingredients. Maeve's chef friend Sunil Ranasinghe cooks up the most beautiful pumpkin curry thickened with toasted coconut and ground rice, while Australia's queen of Asian cooking, Charmaine Solomon, shows some shortcuts and tips on making a marvellous Sri Lankan chicken curry. She then shows Maeve how to eat Sri Lankan style - without knives and forks, using stringhoppers to scoop up curry and accompaniments. We see how stringhoppers and hoppers are made - both are made with riceflour - one looks like a little mat of fine noodles, the other like a bowl-shaped pancake, both adored by Sri Lankans. Dessert is the easiest dinner party sweet you'll find - a dense spiced custard made with coconut milk and palm sugar called wattalappam, made to a family recipe by Deborah Solomon.

programme.desc: S1 E1 Tom Allen Dame Mary Berry takes a fond look back at her career in food while bringing viewers incredible mouth-watering recipes to try at home. Mary can trace her passion for outdoor cooking back 80 years, when she became a Girl Guide. Her friend, comedian Tom Allen, shares her love of the countryside but perhaps not the same aptitude for cooking. Together, they take a leisurely boat ride, sharing tales and facing the odd challenge as Tom attempts to drive the boat and navigate a lock. They stop along the way to cook Mary's classic pan-fried cod, which she learnt to make at college, and the star pudding of Mary's childhood, bread and butter pudding using her mother's recipe, which she still loves eating anywhere. Mary also makes her brand new Thai chicken traybake and her reinvention of her 1970s cottage pie with a modern mash. Spending time with Tom is a chance for Mary to share some rarely seen TV archive footage of her early attempts at outdoor cooking, showing how much things have changed.

programme.desc: S14 E4 London Sarah and Stewart are a couple of cool cats looking for a first home together, for them and their even cooler kittens Jarvis Cocker and Ziggy Stardust. They're determined to stay around their current stomping ground of Finsbury Park, where they've been living their dream lifestyle. They know they're nearly ready to move on to the next stage of their life as a couple, so they want two bedrooms as well as outside space for the cats. But with a budget of 230,000 pounds that's looking like a completely impossible task in this pricey London patch. Happily, they say they're prepared to compromise on almost anything so long as they can stay within their dream area, until Phil starts showing them the reality of what their money can buy, that is. Meanwhile, Kirstie has her hands full finding a home for Louise and Matt, who've never lived full-time in the same city before - let alone the same house, despite having been together for four years. Louise works in London while Matt works in Lincolnshire, and they only spend time together at the weekends. They currently live in the south of the city, and the added commuting time is costing them precious together time. So they want to move north of the river - anywhere north of the river. Even with 350,000 pounds to spend, getting two bedrooms and outside space, with added wow factor, kerb appeal, and a swanky area is a real ask. So Kirstie has to play the bad guy and take their expectations down a notch or two from the off. Even that though might not be enough, leading Kristie to take drastic action to get these two into a house of their own.

programme.title: Location Location Location
programme.desc: S14 E5 Southern Counties Brand-new parents Lucy and David want a forever home for themselves and little baby Evie, and with their life savings at stake they're determined to be picky about how they spend their hard-earned budget of 850,000 pounds. From the off though, they're clear that they each put very different things at the top of their individual wish lists. David wants as many bricks as possible for his bucks and would sacrifice location to get a bigger house. Lucy, though, would settle for a smaller house in the right location around Godalming in Surrey. Phil believes Surrey to be one of the hardest counties in the UK to find houses, and with so much riding on this one he's got his work well and truly cut out to please them both. Over the border in Berkshire and Hampshire, Kirstie also has her hands full with Kelly and Emma, looking for their first home together. They have 350,000 pounds to find a house they can both call home after living together in Kelly's previous place. Emma wants a quiet, rural location that offers safety for their cats, while Kelly wants more space inside the house than outside. As the tears start to flow, Kirstie soon learns that as well as money, there is a lot of emotion invested in this hunt. Finding a house that offers both space for Kelly and the right setting for Emma proves a challenge even for Kirstie, but as ever she pulls out all the stops to find a place that will hopefully have them crying with joy.

programme.title: How I Caught the Killer
programme.desc: S3 E10 Unrequited Love When the police are called to a house fire in June 2009, arson is quickly suspected. All four children in the Masud family are critically injured but daughters Maleha and Nabitha succumb to their injuries. The local community is shocked even more, when a 14-year-old boy is arrested and charged with murder.

programme.title: Wives With Knives
programme.desc: S4 E7 Michelle Covington Michelle Covington runs in to an old classmate, Charles Wayne Covington. She's surprised to learn that he's been carrying a torch for her that's been burning for three decades ever since the two met each other in high school. Charles is determined to make the most of this second chance and asks her out on a date. Though reluctant at first, Michelle relents and she's pleasantly surprised when Charles proves himself a doting and overwhelmingly sweet romantic partner. The new couple dates for several months, embarking on a whirlwind romance that sweeps Michelle off her feet. But she comes crashing down to earth when Charles' rampant alcohol use leads to increasingly violent outbursts and a series of flirtatious encounters with a slew of ex-girlfriends. The couple fights and Michelle pleads with Charles to change his ways. But after months of escalating conflict, the arguments take a nearly-deadly turn. One night, Michelle arrives home to find Charles on the phone with an ex-girlfriend. The pair begins arguing. Charles, drunk and belligerent, attacks Michelle by punching and choking her. Fearing for her life, Michelle grabs a paring knife and swings wildly, stabbing Charles in the leg. The amputee, taking a prescribed regimen of medication that includes blood thinners, is at risk of bleeding to death. Michelle pleads with him to stay back but Charles continues to assault her. In a panic, she rips off his prosthetic leg, and throws it outside. When police arrive they find blood everywhere and immediately assume Michelle is the aggressor, considering Charles' physical limitations. But, once the facts come out, Michelle is released from police custody. Just six months after the incident, the couple reconciles and Charles proposes marriage. They remain married to this day.

Each man is trained in self survival, from fixing his truck in sub zero conditions in seconds to escaping from a truck if the ice cracks. programme.title: Outback Truckers

programme.title: Outback Truckers
programme.desc: S8 E8 Episode 8 In central Queensland, husband and wife team Kylie and David Hornick, are feeling the pressure of a looming deadline on a monster job. In the last two days their convoy of trucks has racked up a whopping 2200 kilometres picking up and delivering 1224 head of cattle. Tempers are frayed as they push to meet their 3pm cut off. Trucker Mike Partridge is helping load a vintage 1948 Farmall tractor, one of 9 vintage tractors he's transporting to Western Australia. In Australia's tropical Northern Territory there's storm clouds on the horizon. It's not just rain that's troubling the Water Drillers, the pressure is on this hit and miss operation for the last bore hole to be a success.

programme.title: American Restoration
programme.desc: S4 E22 Break In Rick Dale, one of Pawn Stars' most popular experts, runs Las Vegas based Rick's Restorations, a family business that finds, restores and upcycles cool objects ranging from Cadillacs to Coke Machines. The before and after reveals of his work are always highlights, in part because of the history nuggets Rick Dale shares about each object, whether it's a barber chair or a gas pump. In this spinoff series, featuring the dynamic characters at Rick's workplace, viewers will watch a variety of objects be bought, bartered and transformed, learning the process of restoration; how do you duplicate Coke machine red? Where can you find 1920s tires? A storyteller who works with tools instead of a pen, Rick shares when and why objects were invented, who used them and how fixing or transforming them changes their value.

programme.title: Ice Road Truckers
programme.desc: S9 E1 Crossing Enemy Lines For two months out of every year, a group of exceptional men find their way to the Canadian tundra to undertake one of the most dangerous jobs on earth. In the thick of winter, truckers in giant eighteen wheelers carry vital equipment and supplies to miners hundreds of miles away. In blizzard conditions, these truckers travel over ice roads that often take them over frozen lakes. Each man is trained in self survival, from fixing his truck in sub zero conditions in seconds to escaping from a truck if the ice cracks. On the other end of the journey are miners whose lives depend on the truckers making it to their base, year after year. The episodes will form a narrative arch - taking the viewer on a journey from when the experienced and novice truckers first sign up for the season, to the last truck making it back to base.

programme.title: American Restoration
programme.desc: S4 E22 Break In Rick Dale, one of Pawn Stars' most popular experts, runs Las Vegas based Rick's Restorations, a family business that finds, restores and upcycles cool objects ranging from Cadillacs to Coke Machines. The before and after reveals of his work are always highlights, in part because of the history nuggets Rick Dale shares about each object, whether it's a barber chair or a gas pump. In this spinoff series, featuring the dynamic characters at Rick's workplace, viewers will watch a variety of objects be bought, bartered and transformed, learning the process of restoration; how do you duplicate Coke machine red? Where can you find 1920s tires? A storyteller who works with tools instead of a pen, Rick shares when and why objects were invented, who used them and how fixing or transforming them changes their value.

programme.title: Mary Berry's Quick Cooking
programme.desc: S1 E6 The Airport In this episode Mary is given an access all areas pass as she heads behind the scenes at London Heathrow airport. Where everyone has one eye on the clock and a flight to catch, Mary wants to see how the restaurants and cafes feed the 70 million people that pass through the terminals each year in record breaking time. Mary throws herself into the different roles needed to keep one of the busiest airports in the world fed and running smoothly, including a stint as an airport Fire Fighter. In this episode Mary whips up some wonderful quick delights including a rich Chicken Korma, a delicious Apple Sandwich Cake and some extra special Roast Scallops.

programme.title: Eat Well For Less
programme.desc: S5 E8 Episode 8 This week Gregg and Chris are in West Sussex to help the Blackman family. There's mum Kate who works as a Nursery Practitioner and her 3 daughters, 16-year-old Ellie, 11-year-old Charlotte and Annabelle, 9 and none of them will eat the same thing! With one daughter who is fussy about what she eats, and another who's dairy intolerant and avoids gluten, mum Kate is cooking 4 separate meals every night and unsurprisingly has fallen out of love with cooking. With Kate feeling guilty for relying on convenience food and takeaways, she has turned to Gregg and Chris for help. Can they bring the joy back into Kate's kitchen and stop her reaching for those convenience foods and takeaways? And can our couple of ex-greengrocers get the girls to fall in love with vegetables?

programme.title: Mary Berry at 90: A Lifetime of Cooking
programme.desc: S1 E1 Tom Allen Dame Mary Berry takes a fond look back at her career in food while bringing viewers incredible mouth-watering recipes to try at home. Mary can trace her passion for outdoor cooking back 80 years, when she became a Girl Guide. Her friend, comedian Tom Allen, shares her love of the countryside but perhaps not the same aptitude for cooking. Together, they take a leisurely boat ride, sharing tales and facing the odd challenge as Tom attempts to drive the boat and navigate a lock. They stop along the way to cook Mary's classic pan-fried cod, which she learnt to make at college, and the star pudding of Mary's childhood, bread and butter pudding using her mother's recipe, which she still loves eating anywhere. Mary also makes her brand new Thai chicken traybake and her reinvention of her 1970s cottage pie with a modern mash. Spending time with Tom is a chance for Mary to share some rarely seen TV archive footage of her early attempts at outdoor cooking, showing how much things have changed.

programme.title: The Chocolate Queen

Celebrated pastry chef and famous chocolatier, Tibballs presents an array of incredibly clever and innovative tricks, tips and cheats to bring the wow factor to home baking. Kirsten believes chocolate is the key to happiness, and with a selection of delectable desserts easy to recreate in home kitchens, she may just be right. Kirsten is sharing recipes and techniques for everything from a next-level take on white chocolate & peanut parfait to her rich chocolate flan. In series three of The Chocolate Queen, Tibballs shares a wealth of knowledge as she works through a huge range of recipes, ensuring even beginner bakers can successfully enjoy her creations at home.

programme.title: Mary Berry at 90: A Lifetime of Cooking
programme.desc: S1 E1 Tom Allen Dame Mary Berry takes a fond look back at her career in food while bringing viewers incredible mouth-watering recipes to try at home. Mary can trace her passion for outdoor cooking back 80 years, when she became a Girl Guide. Her friend, comedian Tom Allen, shares her love of the countryside but perhaps not the same aptitude for cooking. Together, they take a leisurely boat ride, sharing tales and facing the odd challenge as Tom attempts to drive the boat and navigate a lock. They stop along the way to cook Mary's classic pan-fried cod, which she learnt to make at college, and the star pudding of Mary's childhood, bread and butter pudding using her mother's recipe, which she still loves eating anywhere. Mary also makes her brand new Thai chicken traybake and her reinvention of her 1970s cottage pie with a modern mash. Spending time with Tom is a chance for Mary to share some rarely seen TV archive footage of her early attempts at outdoor cooking, showing how much things have changed.

programme.desc: S1 E1 Episode 1 Nigella explains how captivated she was with a recipe she heard about on Twitter, a dish where all the ingredients were familiar, but the finished article unlike anything she had tried before.

programme.title: Rick Stein's Cornwall
programme.desc: S2 E12 Episode 12 Following in the footsteps of Turner, one of Britain's most loved artists, Rick discovers how much the Cornish landscape influenced his work. At Newlyn Fish Market Rick counts in the daily catch with the head auctioneer who tells him how the market has adapted to modern times. Surrounded by beautifully fresh fish, Rick takes away some monkfish and fires up his BBQ to make a grillade of monkfish with roasted red pepper sauce. At Caerhays Castle, home to the nation's largest collection of Magnolia plants, Rick discovers how this corner of Cornwall was once home to some of the great Victorian plant hunters.

programme.title: Food Safari
programme.desc: S2 E7 Croatian This program delves into the delicious world of Croatian food and Maeve enlists her friend Dennis Valcich, chef, author and passionate promoter of the food from his homeland, to run through the key ingredients used in the cuisine. He demonstrates a simple and delicious recipe from his home on the Dalmatian coast - artichoke cooked simply with potatoes and broad beans. Also from Dalmatia, Melbourne chef Ino Kuvacic, from Dalmatino Restaurant, who makes the dish beloved of all - a brodet: fish stew served on polenta. As well as the coastline, the inland of Croatia is represented with a range of smallgoods made by long-time king of Croatian smallgoods Ivan Spehar, who brought the famous skinless sausage cevapcici to many Australians. Home cook and matriarch Branka Roncevic makes the famous cabbage rolls which are served with creamy mashed potato. Her son Frank continues a family tradition of the big Sunday cookout using a bell-shaped Croatian outdoor oven called a peka, which transforms anything cooked in it into a masterpiece. Also using meat and flame, well-known restaurateur Tonci Farac, from Wildfire Restaurant on Sydney's Circular Quay, cooks a magnificent rack of lamb on the barbecue using salt and rosemary to add simple flavours. Prodigious sweets maker Mira Valcich whips up simple biscuits with a plum jam filling to finish.

programme.title: Food Safari
programme.desc: S2 E8 Singaporean This program sizzles with colour, flavour and texture as it savours the wonderful complexity of Singaporean food. Maeve meets up with two Singaporean friends to guide her through the range of ingredients: passionate home cook Helina Lee picks the top spices and sauces needed, while chef Alex Lee (Ginger and Spice, Singapore restaurant) shows off the range of fresh produce and seafood including mud crabs - which he transforms into the famous Singapore chilli mud crab with a surprise key ingredient. Top chef Chui Lee Luk from the acclaimed Claude's restaurant is better known for her French-style food, though away from work she makes a marvellous Assam fish, adapting her mother's treasured recipe. Barrister Tiffany Wong, one of the descendants of a famous Hainanese family, shows how to make beautifully tender Hainan chicken with chicken rice, served with fresh ginger and chilli sauces. Helina Lee whips up a fast salad snack beloved of Singaporeans called rojak. Along the way, we spend time with a Singaporean chef who almost dances as he juggles woks and flame at breakneck speed, and we learn about the love of hawker stalls serving beloved specials. Chef and cooking teacher Chee Ong then demonstrates a stylish take on the famous bubur cha-cha - a dessert of tropical fruit, tapioca and sweet potato that is simply divine.

programme.desc: S3 E5 Episode 5 Returning for a third season, Kirsten Tibballs, aka The Chocolate Queen is back! Celebrated pastry chef and famous chocolatier, Tibballs presents an array of incredibly clever and innovative tricks, tips and cheats to bring the wow factor to home baking. Kirsten believes chocolate is the key to happiness, and with a selection of delectable desserts easy to recreate in home kitchens, she may just be right. Kirsten is sharing recipes and techniques for everything from a next-level take on white chocolate & peanut parfait to her rich chocolate flan. In series three of The Chocolate Queen, Tibballs shares a wealth of knowledge as she works through a huge range of recipes, ensuring even beginner bakers can successfully enjoy her creations at home.

And Rick takes to the waves with an inspirational organisation who offer therapy using the power of surfing.

programme.title: Food Safari
programme.desc: S2 E9 Hungarian This program revels in centuries-old dishes cooked by passionate chefs and home cooks as it explores Hungarian cuisine. Maeve meets up with chef Stephen Oroszvari who has a one-man mission to excite the world about the flavours of his homeland. For instance, did you know that Hungarians are so passionate about paprika, that they have nicknames for some of their favourite varieties? 'Strong Stephen' and 'Gentle Anna' are just two. Long-time restaurateur Csaba Cserfalvi shares tips on making the perfect schnitzel and also shows how deeply committed Hungarians are to their carbs with a deep-fried langos bread and many variations on potatoes. Sport guru Les Murray shares the recipe for his mother's rakott krumpli, layered potatoes with csabai sausage and sour cream, and we join a mad, wonderful goulash cook-off, followed by Stephen's beautiful recipe for Porkolt, a form of goulash served with nokedli, or homemade pasta. The episode soars to a sweet, magnificent crescendo with some of the most exquisite delights made by artisans who have perfected strudels and layered cakes, beigli and tortes. Then, food editor and broadcaster Janelle Bloom shares her grandmother's recipe for wicked cream cheese and sour cherry strudel.

programme.title: Food Safari
programme.desc: S2 E10 Sri Lankan This program explores the colourful fresh flavours and seductive charm of Sri Lankan cooking. Maeve visits a fragrant spice emporium with top Australian Sri Lankan chef Peter Kuruvita, from Flying Fish restaurant, who hones in on the essentials. He whips up an elegant prawn curry with a creamy coconut sauce. We meet caterer, food reviewer and tour guide Paul Van Reyk who demonstrates how to grate a fresh coconut and uses it to make a simple vibrant sambol with a touch of chilli and a delicious, fresh green stir-fry with a handful of ingredients. Maeve's chef friend Sunil Ranasinghe cooks up the most beautiful pumpkin curry thickened with toasted coconut and ground rice, while Australia's queen of Asian cooking, Charmaine Solomon, shows some shortcuts and tips on making a marvellous Sri Lankan chicken curry. She then shows Maeve how to eat Sri Lankan style - without knives and forks, using stringhoppers to scoop up curry and accompaniments. We see how stringhoppers and hoppers are made - both are made with riceflour - one looks like a little mat of fine noodles, the other like a bowl-shaped pancake, both adored by Sri Lankans. Dessert is the easiest dinner party sweet you'll find - a dense spiced custard made with coconut milk and palm sugar called wattalappam, made to a family recipe by Deborah Solomon.

programme.title: Heart Eyes
programme.desc: A masked maniac with glowing red eyes returns each Valentine's Day to kill couples. An ad exec and her romantic colleague become targets and vow to stop the terror.

programme.title: Inferno
programme.desc: The famous symbologist Robert Langdon wakes up in an Italian hospital with amnesia and finds himself the target of a manhunt. Langdon teams up with Sienna Brooks; a doctor he hopes will help him recover his memories. Together, they race across Europe and against the clock to stop a virus that would wipe out half of the world's population.

programme.title: Bumblebee
programme.desc: Cybertron has fallen. When Optimus Prime sends Bumblebee to protect Earth, he begins his journey to become the hero the Universe needs. Crash landing, with no memory of his past, Bumblebee takes refuge in a junkyard disguised as a VW Beetle. Charlie (Hailee Steinfeld), a teenager trying to find her place in the world, discovers and repairs the battle-scarred robot. When the Decepticons forge an alliance with a secret agency led by Agent Burns (John Cena) to hunt down the remaining Autobots, Bumblebee and Charlie team up to protect the world in an action-packed adventure filled with humour and heart that's fun for the whole family.

programme.title: Cliffhanger
programme.desc: Gabe Walker is a member of the mountain-climbing rescue team. While crossing a ledge 1220m above the Earth, Gabe's friend's equipment fails and she slips out of his hand, falling to her death. Almost a year after, he must return to those dreaded peaks, where he finds himself trapped in a desperate battle against ruthless criminals, unforgiving nature and himself.

programme.title: Pulp Fiction
programme.desc: Winnfield and Vincent Vega are two hitmen out to retrieve a suitcase stolen from their employer, mob boss Marcellus Wallace. Wallace has also asked Vincent to take his wife Mia out a few days later when Wallace himself will be out of town. Butch Coolidge is an ageing boxer who is paid by Wallace to lose his next fight. Honey Bunny and Pumpkin are a couple of young lovers and small time thieves who decide they need a change of venue. The lives of these seemingly unrelated people are woven together in a wildly entertaining and exhilarating motion picture adventure that both thrills and amuses.

programme.title: Salt
programme.desc: Phillip Noyce directs Angelina Jolie as Evelyn Salt, a CIA officer who swore an oath to duty, honour and country. When she is accused by a defector of being a Russian sleeper spy, Salt goes on the run to clear her name and ultimately prove her loyalty. Using all her skills and years of experience as a covert operative, she must elude capture and protect her family or the world's most powerful forces will erase any trace of her existence. With her superiors convinced she's out to assassinate the president, she also must race the clock to learn the identity of the real traitor.

programme.title: The Friend
programme.desc: A solitary writer adopts her late friend's Great Dane and, through their bond, starts to come to terms with her past and reconnect with her creative self.

programme.title: Dog Man
programme.desc: Dog Man, part dog, part man, is on a mission to protect and serve while chasing down the feline supervillain, Petey the Cat.

programme.title: The Scorpion King
programme.desc: In this prequel to the blockbuster Mummy films, a mercenary is hired by a dissident alliance to kill the beautiful sorceress Cassandra, from whom the brutal tyrant Memnon draws his strength. Once Cassandra is removed the alliance plans to face Memnon's armies on their own terms, but the sorceress is not all she seems in this swirling, CGI-laden romp.

programme.title: Star Trek
programme.desc: The greatest adventure of all time begins with a young crew's maiden voyage on board the most advanced starship ever created: the USS Enterprise. In the midst of an incredible journey full of optimism, intrigue, comedy and cosmic peril, the new recruits must find a way to stop an evil being whose mission of vengeance threatens all of mankind. The fate of the galaxy rests in the hands of bitter rivals born worlds apart.

programme.title: The Hunt for Red October
programme.desc: A new, technologically superior Soviet nuclear sub, the Red October, is heading for the US coast under the command of Captain Marko Ramius. The American government thinks Ramius is planning to attack. A lone CIA analyst has a different idea: he thinks Ramius is planning to defect, but he has only a few hours to find him and prove it - because the entire Russian naval and air commands are trying to find him, too. The hunt is on.

programme.title: Patriot Games
programme.desc: Former CIA analyst Jack Ryan travels to London with his wife and child. Upon being caught in the middle of a terrorist attack on a member of the royal family, Ryan helps to thwart the assailants. Ryan's courageous act, however, marks him and his family as a target for revenge in the sights of the terrorist whose brother Ryan killed.

programme.title: The Hangover
programme.desc: Two days before his wedding, Doug and his three friends drive to Las Vegas for a blow-out bachelor party they'll never forget. But, in fact, when the three groomsmen wake up the next morning, they can't remember a thing. For some reason, they find a tiger in the bathroom and a six-month-old baby in the closet of their suite at Caesars Palace. The one thing they can't find is Doug. With no clue as to what transpired and little time to spare, the trio must retrace their hazy steps and all their bad decisions in order to figure out where things went wrong and hopefully get Doug back to LA in time to walk down the aisle.

programme.title: The Hangover Part II
programme.desc: Phil, Stu and their mates travel to Thailand for Stu's subdued pre-wedding brunch after the unforgettable bachelor party in Vegas. However, things don't go to plan.

programme.title: The Hangover Part III
programme.desc: The third and final instalment in the comedy smash hit. This time, there's no wedding. No bachelor party. What could go wrong, right? But when the Wolfpack hits the road, all bets are off.

programme.title: Dr. Seuss' the Lorax
programme.desc: Dr. Seuss' The Lorax is an adaptation of Dr. Seuss' classic tale of a forest creature who shares the enduring power of hope. In the walled city of Thneed-Ville, where everything is artificial and even the air is a commodity, a boy named Ted hopes to win the heart of his dream girl, Audrey. When he learns of her wish to see a real tree, Ted seeks out the Once-ler, a ruined old businessman outside of town in a stark wasteland. Upon hearing of how the hermit gave into his greed for profits and devastated the land over the protests of the Lorax, Ted is inspired to undo the disaster. However, the greedy Mayor of Thneed-Ville, Aloysius O'Hare, has made his fortune exploiting the environmental collapse and is determined to stop the boy from undermining his business.

programme.title: Transformers One
programme.desc: The untold origin story of Optimus Prime and Megatron, better known as sworn enemies, but who once were friends bonded like brothers.

programme.title: Piece by Piece
programme.desc: LEGO bricks tell the life story of singer, songwriter and record producer Pharrell Williams - from his childhood in Virginia to his success in the music and fashion industry.

programme.title: Emma.
programme.desc: Jane Austen's beloved comedy about finding your equal and earning your happy ending is reimagined in this delicious film adaptation.

programme.title: Rambo III
programme.desc: Rambo has withdrawn to a Buddhist monastery in Thailand, but his mentor, Colonel Trautman, asks him to help carry out a dangerous mission in Afghanistan. The Vietnam vet refuses. He has found peace, serenity, and is non-violent. Trautman attempts the mission alone, but is captured by the Soviets and is harshly interrogated by the cruel Colonel Zaysen. The CIA can do nothing and call upon Rambo. He needs a few moments to choose his weapons and bind his muscles before hitting his enemies like a hurricane, and in a few days he ravages the country.

programme.title: Jumanji: Welcome to the Jungle
programme.desc: In the brand new adventure Jumanji: Welcome to the Jungle, the tables are turned as four teenagers are sucked into the world of Jumanji. When four high-school kids discover an old video game console with a game they've never heard of Jumanji they are immediately drawn into the game's jungle setting, literally becoming the avatars they chose: gamer Spencer becomes a brawny adventurer; football jock Fridge loses (in his words) 'the top two feet of his body' and becomes an Einstein; popular girl Bethany becomes a middle-aged male professor; and wallflower Martha becomes a badass warrior. What they discover is that you don't just play Jumanji you must survive it. To beat the game and return to the real world, they'll have to go on the most dangerous adventure of their lives, discover what Alan Parrish left 20 years ago, and change the way they think about themselves or they'll be stuck in the game forever.

programme.title: Back to the Future
programme.desc: Marty McFly, a typical American teenager of the 1980s, is accidentally sent back to 1955 in a plutonium-powered DeLorean time machine, invented by a slightly mad scientist. During his often hysterical but amazing trip back in time, Marty must make certain his teenage parents-to-be meet and fall in love so that he can get back to the future.

programme.title: The Karate Kid: Part III
programme.desc: A bad guy from the original Karate Kid plots revenge on young Daniel and his mentor Miyagi after they defeat his karate school and ruin his business.

programme.title: Back To The Future III
programme.desc: Marty McFly ends up in the wild west of 1885 to save mad scientist Doc Brown from a crazed gunfighter.

programme.title: Fast & Furious 6
programme.desc: Hobbs has been tracking an organisation of lethally skilled drivers, whose mastermind is aided by the love Dom thought was dead, Letty. The only way to stop the criminal mercenaries from stealing a top-secret weapon is to outmatch them at street level, so Hobbs asks for the help of Dom and his elite team.

programme.title: Rambo III
programme.desc: Rambo has withdrawn to a Buddhist monastery in Thailand, but his mentor, Colonel Trautman, asks him to help carry out a dangerous mission in Afghanistan. The Vietnam vet refuses. He has found peace, serenity, and is non-violent. Trautman attempts the mission alone, but is captured by the Soviets and is harshly interrogated by the cruel Colonel Zaysen. The CIA can do nothing and call upon Rambo. He needs a few moments to choose his weapons and bind his muscles before hitting his enemies like a hurricane, and in a few days he ravages the country.

programme.title: Cold Pursuit
programme.desc: Welcome to Kehoe, it's -10 degrees and counting at this glitzy ski resort in the Rocky Mountains. The local police aren't used to much action until the son of unassuming town snowplough driver, Nels Coxman, is murdered at the order of Viking, a flamboyant drug lord. Fuelled by rage and armed with heavy machinery, Nels sets out to dismantle the cartel one man at a time, but his understanding of murder comes mainly from what he read in a crime novel. As the bodies pile up, his actions ignite a turf war between Viking and his long-standing rival White Bull, a soulful Native-American mafia boss, that will quickly escalate and turn the small town's bright white slopes blood-red.

programme.title: Back to the Future
programme.desc: Marty McFly, a typical American teenager of the 1980s, is accidentally sent back to 1955 in a plutonium-powered DeLorean time machine, invented by a slightly mad scientist. During his often hysterical but amazing trip back in time, Marty must make certain his teenage parents-to-be meet and fall in love so that he can get back to the future.

programme.title: My Penguin Friend
programme.desc: Inspired by a true story, an enchanting adventure about a lost penguin rescued from an oil spill, who transforms the life of a heartbroken fisherman. They soon become unlikely friends, so bonded that even the vast ocean cannot divide them.

programme.title: The Fast and the Furious
programme.desc: On the turbo-charged streets of Los Angeles, every night is a championship race. With nitro-boosted fury, Dominic Toretto rules the road, turning all his challengers into dust. He and his rival, Johnny Tran, are the boldest, the baddest, and the best, but now there's new rage on the road. They know he's tough, they know he's fast, but what they don't know is that he's a speed demon detective with enough drive and determination to come out the winner.

programme.title: The Phoenician Scheme
programme.desc: Wealthy tycoon Zsa-zsa Korda names his nun daughter sole heir. As he starts a new venture, they face threats from scheming rivals, terrorists, and assassins.

programme.title: The Last Gunfight
programme.desc: Top assassins battle in a brutal underground tournament, but a rogue crew aims to survive, outsmart the killers, and bring down the mastermind behind it all.

programme.title: Hot Fuzz
programme.desc: Nicholas Angel is a big-city cop who can't be stopped - but he's making everyone else on the force look bad. When he is reassigned to a small, quiet town, he struggles with this new, seemingly idyllic world and his bumbling partner. But their dull existence is interrupted by several grisly and suspicious accidents, and the crime-fighting duo turn up the heat and hand out high-octane, car-chasing, gun-fighting, big-city justice.

programme.title: Transformers: Age of Extinction
programme.desc: This film begins after an epic battle left a great city torn, but with the world saved. As humanity picks up the pieces, a shadowy group reveals itself in an attempt to control the direction of history ... while an ancient, powerful new menace sets Earth in its crosshairs. With help from a new cast of humans, Optimus Prime and the Autobots rise to meet their most fearsome challenge yet. In an incredible adventure, they are swept up in a war of good and evil, ultimately leading to a climactic battle across the world.

programme.title: Jurassic World: Rebirth
programme.desc: Zora Bennett leads a team to a deadly island lab to retrieve dinosaur DNA with life-saving potential, but they uncover a shocking secret buried for decades.

programme.title: Star Trek Into Darkness
programme.desc: When the crew of the Enterprise is called back home, they find an unstoppable force of terror from within their own organisation has detonated the fleet and everything it stands for, leaving our world in a state of crisis. With a personal score to settle, Captain Kirk leads a manhunt to a war zone world to capture a one man weapon of mass destruction. As our heroes are propelled into an epic chess game of life and death, love will be challenged, friendships will be torn apart, and sacrifices must be made for the only family Kirk has left: his crew.

programme.title: It Ends with Us
programme.desc: Lily overcomes a traumatic childhood to embark on a new life. A meeting with a neurosurgeon sparks a connection but Lily begins to see sides of him that remind her of her parents' relationship.

programme.title: The Invitation
programme.desc: After the death of her mother, Evie is approached by an unknown cousin who invites her to a lavish wedding in the English countryside. Soon, she realises a gothic conspiracy is afoot and must fight for survival as she uncovers twisted secrets in her family's history.

programme.title: The Ugly Truth
programme.desc: In this wildly funny battle of the sexes, Abby, a successful morning show producer, is looking for a lot in a man. Mike, her obnoxious TV star, knows men only want one thing. Determined to prove that she's not romantically challenged, Abby takes Mike's advice during a promising new romance, but the unexpected results will stun everyone.

programme.title: Wolf Man
programme.desc: Blake and his family barricade themselves in a farmhouse after an unseen creature attacks. As the night unfolds, Blake transforms into a dangerous being, threatening his wife and daughter.

programme.title: Trolls World Tour
programme.desc: Poppy and Branch discover that there are six different troll tribes scattered over six different lands. Each tribe is also devoted to six different kinds of music - funk, country, techno, classical, pop and rock. When rockers Queen Barb and King Thrash set out to destroy the other music, Poppy and Branch embark on a daring mission to unite the trolls and save the diverse melodies from becoming extinct.

programme.title: Back To The Future II
programme.desc: Marty McFly returns, this time travelling forward to 2015 with wacky Doc Brown to save his kids. Their crazy time-travels have a mind-bending effect on history.

programme.title: It Ends with Us
programme.desc: Lily overcomes a traumatic childhood to embark on a new life. A meeting with a neurosurgeon sparks a connection but Lily begins to see sides of him that remind her of her parents' relationship.

programme.title: Robin Hood (2010)

programme.desc: Megamind is the most brilliant super-villain the world has ever known, and the least successful. Over the years he has tried to conquer Metro City in every imaginable way. Suddenly, the fate of Metro City is threatened when a new villain arrives and chaos runs rampant, leaving everyone to wonder: can the world's biggest 'mind' actually save the day?

programme.title: The Pirates Who Don't Do Anything
programme.desc: Those vegie-eating boys are back. Three veggies serve as 'cabin boys' at a pirate-themed dinner theatre, where they long to move from table service to the stage show, but their incompetence, laziness and cowardice get in the way. But when a princess drags them into the 17th century to rescue her brother, who's been kidnapped by a nefarious pirate with designs on her kingdom, they have to overcome their issues and become heroes.

programme.title: Penguins of Madagascar
programme.desc: Recruited from youngsters into the global spy game, four penguins are called into action by a mysterious espionage organisation in order to save the world from a villainous octopus.

programme.title: Balto
programme.desc: Part husky/part wolf, Balto doesn't know where he belongs. He's an outcast in Alaska, except to his true friends - Boris, the Russian snow goose; polar bear cubs Muk and Luk; and the beautiful husky, Jenna. Even though he's different, all of Balto's friends recognise what he still can't see himself: his noble spirit. One day, a serious diphtheria epidemic spreads fast among the children of Nome. When a fierce blizzard closes off all routes of transport, there's no way to obtain lifesaving medicine unless a team of sled dogs can race six-hundred miles through the blinding Arctic storm and bring back anti-toxin. But when the dogs get lost in the frozen wilderness, only Balto can rescue the team and save the children.

programme.title: Paddington
programme.desc: This film tells the story of the comic misadventures of a young Peruvian bear who travels to the city in search of a home. Finding himself lost and alone, he begins to realise that city life is not all he had imagined until he meets the kindly Brown family who read the label around his neck that says \.

programme.title: Paddington 2
programme.desc: Now happily settled with the Brown family, Paddington picks up a series of odd jobs to buy the perfect present for his Aunt Lucy's 100th birthday, only for the gift to be stolen.

programme.title: Antz
programme.desc: A worker ant changes roles with a soldier ant to woo a forbidden princess.

programme.title: Jumanji: Welcome to the Jungle
programme.desc: In the brand new adventure Jumanji: Welcome to the Jungle, the tables are turned as four teenagers are sucked into the world of Jumanji. When four high-school kids discover an old video game console with a game they've never heard of Jumanji they are immediately drawn into the game's jungle setting, literally becoming the avatars they chose: gamer Spencer becomes a brawny adventurer; football jock Fridge loses (in his words) 'the top two feet of his body' and becomes an Einstein; popular girl Bethany becomes a middle-aged male professor; and wallflower Martha becomes a badass warrior. What they discover is that you don't just play Jumanji you must survive it. To beat the game and return to the real world, they'll have to go on the most dangerous adventure of their lives, discover what Alan Parrish left 20 years ago, and change the way they think about themselves or they'll be stuck in the game forever.

programme.title: The Colours Within
programme.desc: A girl who can see colours in people's hearts joins a band with two other people.

programme.title: Bee Movie
programme.desc: A bee is abuzz over a scandal: people are stealing honey to eat. With the help of a florist, he sues the human race for 'honey laundering'.

programme.title: Curious George: Cape Ahoy
programme.desc: With help from a local fisherman, his niece and an adorable baby seal, George embarks on a quest in search of the long-lost shipwreck of legendary sea captain Trumpet Tooter.

programme.title: E.T. the Extra-Terrestrial
programme.desc: While visiting the Earth at Night, a group of alien botanists is discovered and disturbed by an approaching human task force. Because of the more than hasty take-off, one of the visitors is left behind. The little alien finds himself all alone on a very strange planet. Fortunately, the extra-terrestrial soon finds a friend and emotional companion in 10-year-old Elliot, who discovered him looking for food in his family's garden shed. While E.T. slowly gets acquainted with Elliot's brother Michael, his sister Gertie as well as with Earth customs, members of the task force work day and night to track down the whereabouts of Earth's first visitor from Outer Space.

programme.title: The Secret Garden (2020)
programme.desc: When Mary Lennox's parents suddenly die, she is sent to live with her uncle, Archibald Craven, on his remote country estate deep in the Yorkshire moors. While exploring, she discovers a hidden magical garden.

programme.title: Major Payne
programme.desc: When peace breaks out in America, killing machine Major Benson Winifred Payne, United States Marine Corps Special Forces, is given his marching orders: to the unemployment line. Unable to cope with civilian life, Payne is thrust back into the military regiment as commander of the Madison Academy Junior ROTC.

programme.title: Kung Fu Panda 3
programme.desc: When Po's long-lost panda father suddenly reappears, the reunited duo travels to a secret panda paradise to meet scores of hilarious new panda characters. When the supernatural villain Kai begins to sweep across China defeating all the kung fu masters, Po must do the impossible: learn to train a village full of his fun-loving, clumsy brethren to become the ultimate band of kung fu pandas.

programme.title: Jurassic Park III
programme.desc: Desperate to find their missing son, Paul and his wife Amanda trick eminent palaeontologist Dr Alan Grant into accompanying them to Isla Sorna. The small team embark on a dangerous task, searching through a deserted island inhabited by ferocious dinosaurs.

programme.title: The Secret Life of Pets 2
programme.desc: Terrier Max is coping with some major life changes. His owner is now married and has a toddler, Liam. Max is so worried about protecting the boy that he develops a nervous tic. On a family trip to a farm, Max and mutt Duke encounter canine-intolerant cows, hostile foxes and a terrifying turkey, all of which only elevates Max's anxiety. Luckily, Max gets some guidance from veteran farm dog Rooster, who pushes Max to ditch his neuroses, find his inner alpha and give Liam a little more freedom.

programme.title: Khumba
programme.desc: Rejected by his superstitious herd, a half-striped zebra embarks on a daring quest to earn his stripes but finds the courage and self-acceptance to save all the animals of the Great Karoo.

programme.title: The Road to El Dorado
programme.desc: Get ready for an exhilarating ride of a lifetime! Join Tulio and Miguel and their hilarious horse Altivo as they set sail, map in hand, in search of golden treasure in the all-star adventure, The Road to El Dorado! Upon landing on the shores of El Dorado, the legendary Lost City of Gold, Tulio and Miguel are mistaken for gods and are lavished with riches beyond their wildest dreams! As friendship, loyalty, and greed collide, our unlikely heroes must make the decision of their lives: run off with the gold or face unforeseen dangers to save the people of El Dorado.

programme.title: Shrek
programme.desc: An ogre, with the help of an annoying donkey, tries to win back his swamp by returning a princess to a scheming lord.

programme.title: The Croods
programme.desc: This film tells the story of the world's first family road trip. When their cave is destroyed, the Crood family must embark on a comedy adventure into strange and spectacular territory in search of a new home. As if patriarch Grug didn't already have enough to handle, it goes from bad to worse when they encounter an imaginative nomad named Guy. With Guy's help the Croods conquer their fear of the outside world and discover that they have exactly what it takes to survive - each other.

programme.title: Curious George: Cape Ahoy
programme.desc: With help from a local fisherman, his niece and an adorable baby seal, George embarks on a quest in search of the long-lost shipwreck of legendary sea captain Trumpet Tooter.

programme.title: Despicable Me
programme.desc: In a happy suburban neighbourhood surrounded by white picket fences and flowering rose bushes sits a black house with a dead lawn. Unbeknownst to the neighbours, hidden deep beneath this home is a vast secret hideout belonging to Gru, a dastardly villain who, along with the help of his many little minions, is planning the biggest heist in the history of the world: he's going to steal the moon!

programme.title: Despicable Me 2
programme.desc: Gru, his adorable girls, and the mischievous Minions are back with a cast of unforgettable new characters in the blockbuster sequel to the worldwide phenomenon. Just as Gru has given up being super-bad to be a super-dad, the Anti-Villain League recruits him to track down a new criminal mastermind and save the world. Partnered with secret agent Lucy Wilde, Gru, along with the wildly unpredictable Minions, must figure out how to keep his cover while also keeping up with his duties as a father. Get ready for more Minion madness.

programme.title: Despicable Me 3
programme.desc: After he is fired from the Anti-Villain League for failing to take down the latest bad guy to threaten humanity, Gru finds himself in the middle of a major identity crisis. When a mysterious stranger shows up to inform Gru that he has a long-lost twin brother who desperately wishes to follow in his twin's despicable footsteps, one former supervillain will rediscover just how good it feels to be bad.

programme.title: How the Grinch Stole Christmas
programme.desc: He's mean and green and he hates the yo-ho-hoing. The Grinch conspires to steal Christmas from Whoville, making off with the presents, decorations, trees and every other joyful thing.

programme.title: Early Man
programme.desc: Set at the dawn of time when prehistoric creatures roamed the earth, Early Man tells the story of courageous caveman Dug and his sidekick Hognob who, together with their fearless new friend Goona, must unite their Stone Age Tribe against the mighty Bronze Age enemy, Lord Nooth.

programme.title: Jumanji
programme.desc: Young Alan Parrish sits down as a young boy to play a game with his friend, Sarah, and on a roll of the dice is mysteriously transported into the strange jungle realm of Jumanji. There he remains trapped for 26 years, until two newly orphaned children, Judy and Peter, playing in the attic of Alan's childhood home, free the now-adult Alan from the game's clutches. But to defeat Jumanji's encroaching powers, the three reluctant players must find the now-grown Sarah and band together as a makeshift family to finish the game - before it finishes them.

programme.title: Spider-Man: No Way Home
programme.desc: With Spider-Man's identity now revealed, Peter asks Doctor Strange for help. When a spell goes wrong, dangerous foes from other worlds start to appear, forcing Peter to discover what it truly means to be Spider-Man.

programme.title: Sonic The Hedgehog
programme.desc: It's supervillain versus super-sonic in an all-out race across the globe to stop the evil genius Robotnik from using Sonic's power for world domination.

programme.title: The Flintstones
programme.desc: Travel back to the stone-age in this big-budget treatment of the world's favourite prehistoric family! Fred Flintstone, a put-upon blue-collar worker struggling to squeak by, with the help of his best buddy Barney and his wife Wilma. After an aptitude test mix up, Fred Flintstone trades his job as Slate & Company Bronto-crane operator for a vice presidency. But there's trouble brewing in Bedrock: An evil executive and his sinister secretary are now plotting to use Fred as the fall guy in an embezzlement scheme!

programme.title: Sinbad: Legend of the Seven Seas
programme.desc: It's high-seas adventure when legendary swashbuckler Sinbad, his loyal pooch Spike, and the daring Princess Marina face off against the trickster Goddess of Chaos and her mischievous monsters.

programme.title: An American Tail
programme.desc: Fievel the mouse travels from Russia to America with his family in the late 1800s to seek freedom from cat persecution.

programme.title: The Secret Life of Pets
programme.desc: Taking place in a Manhattan apartment building, Max's life as a favourite pet is turned upside down, when his owner brings home a sloppy mongrel named Duke. They have to put their quarrels behind when they find out that an adorable white bunny named Snowball is building an army of lost pets determined to take revenge.

programme.title: The Wild Robot
programme.desc: Shipwrecked on a deserted island, a robot named Roz must learn to adapt to its new surroundings. Building relationships with the native animals, Roz soon develops a parental bond with an orphaned gosling.

programme.title: The Smurfs
programme.desc: When the evil wizard Gargamel chases the tiny blue Smurfs out of their village, they tumble from their magical world into the middle of Central Park, but they must find a way back before he tracks them down.

programme.title: The Smurfs 2
programme.desc: Evil wizard Gargamel creates a couple of mischievous Smurf-like creatures called the Naughties hoping they will let him harness the magical Smurf-essence. However, he soon discovers that he needs the help of Smurfette, who knows the secret to turning the Naughties into real Smurfs. When Gargamel and his Naughties kidnap Smurfette from Smurf Village and bring her to Paris, it's up to Papa, Clumsy, Grouchy and Vanity to reunite with their human friends, Patrick and Grace Winslow, and rescue her!

programme.title: Venom: The Last Dance
programme.desc: Eddie Brock and Venom must make a devastating decision as they're pursued by a mysterious military man and alien monsters from Venom's home world.

programme.title: Wanted
programme.desc: Wesley's life is over, his pathetic old one, anyway. Fortunately, it is all because of a girl. Enter sizzling-hot Fox, who crashes into his life and introduces him to the Fraternity, a secret society of assassins, led by the enigmatic Sloan. Seems Wes's long-lost father was killed while working for the Fraternity and Wes has been selected to target the rogue member who murdered him. But before he can complete his assignment, Wes must first uncover the dark secrets behind the Fraternity in order to determine his own destiny.

programme.title: Bumblebee
programme.desc: Cybertron has fallen. When Optimus Prime sends Bumblebee to protect Earth, he begins his journey to become the hero the Universe needs. Crash landing, with no memory of his past, Bumblebee takes refuge in a junkyard disguised as a VW Beetle. Charlie (Hailee Steinfeld), a teenager trying to find her place in the world, discovers and repairs the battle-scarred robot. When the Decepticons forge an alliance with a secret agency led by Agent Burns (John Cena) to hunt down the remaining Autobots, Bumblebee and Charlie team up to protect the world in an action-packed adventure filled with humour and heart that's fun for the whole family.

programme.title: Morbius
programme.desc: Biochemist Dr Michael Morbius tries to cure himself of a rare blood disease, but he inadvertently infects himself with a form of vampirism instead.

programme.title: Welcome to the Jungle
programme.desc: Beck is a bounty hunter sent into the treacherous jungles of the Amazon to bring the rebellious Travis back to the States. When Beck and Travis reluctantly join forces to hunt down a priceless treasure, this unlikely team embarks on a pulse-pounding, nonstop thrill ride.

programme.title: Salt
programme.desc: Phillip Noyce directs Angelina Jolie as Evelyn Salt, a CIA officer who swore an oath to duty, honour and country. When she is accused by a defector of being a Russian sleeper spy, Salt goes on the run to clear her name and ultimately prove her loyalty. Using all her skills and years of experience as a covert operative, she must elude capture and protect her family or the world's most powerful forces will erase any trace of her existence. With her superiors convinced she's out to assassinate the president, she also must race the clock to learn the identity of the real traitor.

programme.title: Ghost Rider
programme.desc: Johnny Blaze was only a teenage stunt biker when he sold his soul to the devil. Years later, Johnny is a world renowned daredevil by day, but at night, he becomes the Ghost Rider of Marvel Comics legend. The devil's bounty hunter, he is charged with finding evil souls on earth and bringing them to hell. But when a twist of fate brings Johnny's long-lost love back into his life, Johnny realises he just might have a second chance at happiness - if he can beat the devil and win back his soul. To do so he'll have to defeat Blackheart, the devil's nemesis and wayward son, whose plot to take over his father's realm will bring hell on earth - unless Ghost Rider can stop him.

programme.title: Hellboy
programme.desc: Born in hell and bred to be evil, Hellboy was rescued by a benevolent doctor who raised him to be a hero. Now he must thwart a madman who wants to steal his powers and destroy mankind.

programme.title: Bloodshot
programme.desc: Based on the Valiant Comics series, Bloodshot, an ex-killer for the mob and slain soldier, is re-animated with superpowers.

programme.title: Star Trek
programme.desc: The greatest adventure of all time begins with a young crew's maiden voyage on board the most advanced starship ever created: the USS Enterprise. In the midst of an incredible journey full of optimism, intrigue, comedy and cosmic peril, the new recruits must find a way to stop an evil being whose mission of vengeance threatens all of mankind. The fate of the galaxy rests in the hands of bitter rivals born worlds apart.

programme.title: Pacific Rim: Uprising
programme.desc: The globe-spanning conflict between otherworldly monsters of mass destruction and the human-piloted supermachines built to vanquish them was only a prelude to the all-out assault on humanity in \.

programme.title: Transformers: Age of Extinction
programme.desc: This film begins after an epic battle left a great city torn, but with the world saved. As humanity picks up the pieces, a shadowy group reveals itself in an attempt to control the direction of history ... while an ancient, powerful new menace sets Earth in its crosshairs. With help from a new cast of humans, Optimus Prime and the Autobots rise to meet their most fearsome challenge yet. In an incredible adventure, they are swept up in a war of good and evil, ultimately leading to a climactic battle across the world.

programme.title: Miami Vice
programme.desc: When detectives Ricardo Tubbs and Sonny Crockett are asked to investigate the brutal murders of two federal agents, they find themselves pulled into the lethal world of drug traffickers.

programme.title: Jack Ryan: Shadow Recruit
programme.desc: Based on the character created by bestselling author Tom Clancy, Jack Ryan is a global action thriller set in the present day. This original story follows a young Jack as he uncovers a financial terrorist plot. The story follows him from 9/11, through his tour of duty in Afghanistan, which scarred him forever, and into his early days in the Financial Intelligence Unit of the modern CIA where he becomes an analyst, under the guardianship of his handler, Harper. When Ryan believes he's uncovered a Russian plot to collapse the United States economy, he goes from being an analyst to becoming a spy and must fight to save his own life and those of countless others, while also trying to protect the thing that's more important to him than anything, his relationship with his fiancee Cathy.

programme.title: Elysium
programme.desc: In the year 2154, two classes of people exist: the very wealthy, who live on a pristine man-made space station called Elysium, and the rest, who live on an overpopulated, ruined Earth. The people of Earth are desperate to escape the planet's crime and poverty, and they critically need the state-of-the-art medical care available on Elysium - but some in Elysium will stop at nothing to enforce anti-immigration laws and preserve their citizens' luxurious lifestyle. The only man with the chance bring equality to these worlds is Max, an ordinary guy in desperate need to get to Elysium. With his life hanging in the balance, he reluctantly takes on a dangerous mission - one that pits him against Elysium's Secretary Delacourt and her hard-line forces - but if he succeeds, he could save not only his own life, but millions of people on Earth as well.

programme.title: Fast & Furious Presents: Hobbs & Shaw
programme.desc: Hobbs and Shaw, the trash-talking sworn enemies, must team up to take down a cyber-genetically enhanced anarchist with a bio weapon that threatens the fate of humanity.

programme.title: The Mummy (1999)
programme.desc: Adventurer Rick O'Connell and Egyptologist Evelyn Carnahan discover the lost city of Hamunaptra, and struggle to save the world from unspeakable evil after they inadvertently stumble upon a mummy's tomb in 1923, and the mummy is accidentally resurrected.

programme.title: The Mummy Returns
programme.desc: When a chain of events finds the corpse of Imhotep resurrected in the British Museum, the mummy walks the Earth once more, determined to fulfil his quest for immortality. An even more powerful force born of the darkest rituals of ancient Egypt has also been set loose in the world. When these two forces clash, the fate of the world will hang in the balance, sending the O'Connells on a desperate race to save the world.

programme.title: The Mummy: Tomb of the Dragon Emperor
programme.desc: The O'Connells must stop a mummy awoken from a 2000-year-old curse who threatens to plunge the world into his merciless, unending service. Doomed by a wronged sorceress, Zi Yuan, to spend eternity in suspended animation, the ruthless Dragon Emperor and his 10,000 warriors have laid forgotten for eons, entombed in clay as a vast, silent Terracotta Army.

programme.title: Bulletproof
programme.desc: A hilarious saga of a cop, a crook and a beautiful friendship gone sour. Once inseparable pals, Archie Moses and Rock Keats find themselves on opposite sides of the law, each feeling betrayed by the other. In fact, the only person who hates them more than they hate each other is ruthless drug kingpin Frank Colton, who wants to put them both six feet under! Now, through a strange twist of fate, Moses and Keats are on the run - together. With a little luck, the bungling boys just might get out of this one alive ... if they don't kill each other first!

programme.title: Don't Breathe
programme.desc: Rocky, a young woman wanting to start a better life for her and her sister, agrees to take part in the robbery of a house owned by a wealthy blind man with her boyfriend Money and their friend Alex. But when the blind man turns out to be a more than he seems, the group must find a way to escape his home before they become his newest victims.

programme.title: Jack Reacher
programme.desc: A military cop becomes involved in a deadly game of cat-and-mouse when five people are randomly murdered by a sniper.

programme.title: Fast & Furious 5
programme.desc: Dom Toretto and Brian O'Conner lead a reunion of returning all-stars from every chapter of the explosive franchise built on speed to assemble for a high-stakes race that places an unlikely alliance of cops and racers in from Rio de Janeiro. The team must also defeat a corrupt businessman who wants them all dead. A dogged federal agent whose strike team tears through South America in hot pursuit, but soon has a difficult time determining the good men from the bad.

programme.title: Fast & Furious 6
programme.desc: Hobbs has been tracking an organisation of lethally skilled drivers, whose mastermind is aided by the love Dom thought was dead, Letty. The only way to stop the criminal mercenaries from stealing a top-secret weapon is to outmatch them at street level, so Hobbs asks for the help of Dom and his elite team.

programme.title: Battleship
programme.desc: Based on the classic Hasbro naval combat game, this is the story of an international fleet of ships that come across an alien armada while on naval war games exercise.

programme.title: White House Down
programme.desc: Capitol Policeman John Cale has just been denied his dream job with the Secret Service of protecting President James Sawyer. Not wanting to let down his little girl with the news, he takes her on a tour of the White House, during which the complex is overtaken by a heavily armed paramilitary group. Now, with the nation's government falling into chaos and time running out, it's up to Cale to save the president, his daughter, and the country.

programme.title: Death Race 4: Beyond Anarchy
programme.desc: Danny Trejo returns as the ruthless bookie, Goldberg, in the wildest, bloodiest, Death Race ever. After a failed attack on inmate and legendary driver, Frankenstein, Black Ops specialist Connor Gibson (Zach McGowan) infiltrates a super-maximum federal prison with one goal - enter the immoral and illegal Death Race and take Frankenstein down. Connor enlists the help of Baltimore Bob (Danny Glover) and Lists (Fred Koehler), and unexpectedly falls in love with bartending beauty Jane (Christine Marzano). Connor will have to fight for more than his life in this brutal world of no guards, no rules, no track, and no fear.

programme.title: The Fast and the Furious
programme.desc: On the turbo-charged streets of Los Angeles, every night is a championship race. With nitro-boosted fury, Dominic Toretto rules the road, turning all his challengers into dust. He and his rival, Johnny Tran, are the boldest, the baddest, and the best, but now there's new rage on the road. They know he's tough, they know he's fast, but what they don't know is that he's a speed demon detective with enough drive and determination to come out the winner.

programme.title: 2 Fast 2 Furious
programme.desc: It's the nitro-fuelled answer to the question: how fast do you like it? Now an ex-cop on the run, Brian O'Connor hooks into outlaw street-racing. When the Feds strong-arm him back, O'Connor's no rules, win-or-die skills are unleashed against an international drug lord. With his velocity-addicted buddy riding shotgun, and a drop-dead-gorgeous undercover agent dialling up the heat, this film accelerates the action into a desperate race for survival, justice and mind-blowing, jaw-dropping speed.

programme.title: The Fast and the Furious
programme.desc: On the turbo-charged streets of Los Angeles, every night is a championship race. With nitro-boosted fury, Dominic Toretto rules the road, turning all his challengers into dust.
